claim.claim-text:
1. A method of deploying an endograft comprising the steps of:
delivering an endograft to a diseased portion of a body lumen, said endograft being radially constrained by a sheath and select longitudinal portions of said endograft being radially constrained by releasable restraining members operatively associated with said select longitudinal portions of said endograft;
withdrawing said sheath to partially deploy said endograft, wherein said releasable restraining members constrain said selected longitudinal portions of said endograft to provide a flow path external said endograft proximate said restraining members while permitting portions of said endograft intermediate said selected longitudinal portions to expand;
releasing said restraining members to further deploy said select longitudinal portions to fully expand said endograft.

8. An endograft delivery system comprising:
a catheter configured to carry said endograft and to be endoluminally advanced through a body lumen;
a nosecone attached to a proximal end of said catheter;
a sheath configured to constrain said endograft in a radially compressed configuration during endoluminal advancement and to be axially withdrawn from said endograft to partially deploy said endograft; and
at least two releasable restraining members extending over and radially constraining lengthwise portions of said endograft.
